      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a pretty optimistic take. Won't those corporate tax cuts just lead to more stock buybacks and higher executive pay instead of actually boosting wages for regular workers? some economists argue that the trickle-down effect isn't actually real and just makes the gap worse. what do you think about that critique?",
