      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean \"valid concern\" is one way to put it, but isn't it basically a proven fact at this point? like, almost every major study on supply-side economics shows it fails to lift the bottom. isn't it more accurate to say the bill is just going to fail its goal of reducing inequality because of how corporate incentives actually work?",
